<text fill="var(--muted)" font-family="Courier New" font-size="7" id="fb-delay-label" text-anchor="middle" x="265" y="157">200ms</text>
<!-- EQ at bottom-right -->
<circle cx="219" cy="243" fill="var(--surface)" r="22" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.3)" stroke-width="1"></circle>
<text fill="var(--dim)" font-family="Courier New" font-size="8" letter-spacing="0.05em" text-anchor="middle" x="219" y="246">EQ</text>
<!-- REVERB at bottom-left -->
<circle cx="81" cy="243" fill="var(--surface)" r="22" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.3)" stroke-width="1"></circle>
<text fill="var(--dim)" font-family="Courier New" font-size="8" letter-spacing="0.05em" text-anchor="middle" x="81" y="246">REVERB</text>
<!-- OUTPUT at left -->
<circle cx="35" cy="150" fill="var(--surface)" r="22" stroke="rgba(59,130,246,0.3)" stroke-width="1"></circle>
<text fill="var(--dim)" font-family="Courier New" font-size="8" letter-spacing="0.05em" text-anchor="middle" x="35" y="146">OUT</text>
<text fill="var(--muted)" font-family="Courier New" font-size="7" text-anchor="middle" x="35" y="157">→ FB</text>
<!-- Stability dot -->
<circle cx="150" cy="35" fill="rgba(34,197,94,0.8)" id="fb-stability-dot" opacity="0.9" r="7"></circle>
</svg>
<!-- Stability legend -->
<div class="stability-legend">
<div class="stability-item">
<div class="stability-dot" style="background:rgba(34,197,94,0.8);"></div>
<span>STABLE — controlled drone (gain &lt; 50%)</span>
</div>
<div class="stability-item">
<div class="stability-dot" style="background:rgba(245,158,11,0.8);"></div>
<span>RICH — saturating, musical (50–70%)</span>
</div>
<div class="stability-item">
<div class="stability-dot" style="background:rgba(239,68,68,0.8);"></div>
<span>UNSTABLE — risk of overload (&gt; 70%)</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<!-- Controls -->
<div class="card">
<div class="slider-row">
<label>FEEDBACK GAIN</label>
<input id="fb-gain" max="95" min="0" oninput="fbUpdateGain(this.value)" type="range" value="40"/>
<span class="val" id="fb-gain-val">40%</span>
</div>
<div id="fb-zone-label" style="font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:11px;color:rgba(34,197,94,0.9);margin:-8px 0 8px 156px;">
            ◈ STABLE ZONE
          </div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>LOW CUT (EQ)</label>
<input id="fb-lowcut" max="400" min="20" oninput="updateVal(this,'fb-lowcut-val','Hz')" type="range" value="80"/>
<span class="val" id="fb-lowcut-val">80Hz</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>HIGH CUT (EQ)</label>
<input id="fb-highcut" max="8000" min="1000" oninput="updateVal(this,'fb-highcut-val','Hz')" type="range" value="4000"/>
<span class="val" id="fb-highcut-val">4000Hz</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>DELAY TIME</label>
<input id="fb-delay" max="500" min="50" oninput="fbUpdateDelay(this.value)" type="range" value="200"/>
<span class="val" id="fb-delay-val">200ms</span>
</div>
<div class="btn-row">
<button class="btn" id="fb-play-btn" onclick="fbToggle()">▶ START TONE</button>
</div>
<div id="fb-warning" style="font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:11px;color:rgba(239,68,68,0.8);margin-top:8px;opacity:0;transition:opacity 1.5s ease;">
            ⚠ HIGH GAIN — output may saturate
          </div>
</div>
</div>
<p class="info-text hidden stagger-3">
        Controlled feedback was pioneered by Alvin Lucier, Nicolas Collins, and Brian Eno. At stable
        gain levels, the system produces a self-sustaining drone. In the rich zone, harmonics bloom
        as the signal saturates. The EQ in the feedback path shapes which frequencies dominate —
        low-cut pushes toward brilliance; high-cut toward warmth. Lucier's <em>I Am Sitting in a Room</em>
        (1969) used room acoustics as the feedback processor itself.
      </p>
</div>
</section>
